  "comparison": {
    "delta_avg_expansions": 0.89,
    "delta_avg_frontier": 1.44,
    "delta_avg_nodes": 2.89,
    "interpretation": [
      "With 9 concurrent live sessions, none of the sessions completed their first logged expansion within 6 minutes.",
      "With only 3 concurrent live sessions, every group progressed to child creation and at least one logged expansion for most sessions in the same 6-minute window.",
      "Because the scheduler code path was the same in both scenarios and only the number of simultaneously active live sessions changed, the dominant bottleneck is model-service throughput under concurrency, not scheduler bookkeeping alone.",
      "Remaining latency is still meaningful even in the grouped runs, because all grouped sessions stayed busy after 6 minutes; root build plus the first live child proposal batch is still too expensive."
    ]
  }
